Definition: repetition of same sense in different words
Example: `a true fact' and `a free gift' are pleonastic expressions; the phrase `a beginner who has just started' is tautological; at the risk of being redundant I return to my original proposition- J.B.Conant
Synonyms: noun, communication, pleonasm, redundant, attribute, redundancy, act, tautologic, tautology, tautological, repetition, of, same, sense, in, different, words, a, true, fact, and, free, gift, are, expressions, the, phrase, beginner, who, has, just, started, is, at, risk, being, I, return, to, my, original, proposition, -, J, B, Conant
Category: adj.all
